ADDITIONS TO THE ORIGINAL TASK
─────────────────────────────

1. ADD a new field type: "radio"
   - Renders a radio button group from "options" array.
   - Each option has "value" (machine value) and "label" (display).
   - Single selection.
   - Submit collects the chosen value (e.g., "RETURNABLE").

2. CONDITIONAL FIELDS in items_table:
   - The "return_date" column in items has a "conditional" key.
   - Render this column ONLY when the form field named in
     conditional.field equals conditional.value.
   - Example: when requisition_type === "RETURNABLE", show
     return_date column. When "NON_RETURNABLE", hide it.
   - This is a pure CSS/JSX show/hide based on form state — no
     backend round-trip.
   - When the column is hidden, do NOT include return_date in the
     submitted payload (or send it as null — backend ignores).

3. ITEM NAME / CODE field:
   - User types the item code directly (e.g., "04617").
   - No autocomplete or DB lookup from frontend — backend resolves
     the code to item details (name, price, etc.) on submit.
   - If backend can't resolve a code, it returns a field-level error
     for that row (see error handling below).

